<%- include('header') %>

<div class="about-container">
    <h1>About This Project</h1>
    
    <div class="about-content">
        <section>
            <h2>What is EJS Framework?</h2>
            <p>EJS Framework is a modern web application built with Express.js and EJS templating engine. 
            It demonstrates the core concepts of server-side rendering and dynamic page generation.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js with Express.js</li>
                <li><strong>Template Engine:</strong> EJS (Embedded JavaScript)</li>
                <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript</li>
                <li><strong>Data Storage:</strong> In-Memory (Can be extended to use databases)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Project Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ Dynamic page rendering with EJS templates</li>
                <li>✅ Add, view, and delete items</li>
                <li>✅ RESTful API for data retrieval</li>
                <li>✅ Responsive design</li>
                <li>✅ Error handling and 404 pages</li>
                <li>✅ Clean folder structure</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <p>To run this project locally:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Install dependencies: <code>npm install</code></li>
                <li>Start development server: <code>npm run dev</code></li>
                <li>Open: <code>http://localhost:3000</code></li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>

<%- include('footer') %>
